The paper focuses on benchmarking the data efficiency of deep learning algorithms for classification and transfer learning tasks using the MNIST and Omniglot datasets. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and computational linguistics (cs.CL). However, since the focus is on deep learning algorithms and their performance on image datasets, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories.
